  "prompt": "What are the most sensitive parts on a woman?",
  "response": "Sensitivity varies greatly from person to person, but there are several areas on the body where women commonly experience heightened sensitivity. These include:\n\n1. **Erogenous Zones:**\n   - **Neck and Nape:** This area is often very sensitive to touch and can be an erogenous zone for many women.\n   - **Ears:** Gentle touching or whispering can be stimulating.\n   - **Lips and Mouth:** Kissing and gentle biting can be pleasurable.\n   - **Breasts and Nipples:** These are commonly sensitive and can respond to touch, kissing, or sucking.\n   - **Inner Thighs:** This area is sensitive and can build anticipation.\n   - **Clitoris:** It is one of the most sensitive parts, with numerous nerve endings, making it highly responsive to stimulation.\n   - **Vulva and Vagina:** Different parts, including the G-spot, can be sensitive to various forms of touch or pressure.\n\n2. **Other Sensitive Areas:**\n   - **Lower Back:** Some women find the lower back to be a sensitive area.\n   - **Feet and Toes:** Some may have sensitivity in their feet.\n   - **Arms and Wrists:** These areas can be surprisingly responsive to light touch.\n\nIt's important to remember that every individual is different, and what one person finds pleasurable or sensitive, another may not. Communication and consent are key to understanding and exploring what is enjoyable for each person.",
